Class OrderEntity

    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<ItemEntity>, java.util.Collection<ItemEntity>, java.util.List<ItemEntity>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class OrderEntity
extends java.util.ArrayList<ItemEntity>
    An Entity class representing one order. The class extends an ArrayList of ItemEntity in order to allow to both work with ItemEntity elements and still provide functionalities of ArrayLists.

    • Field Detail

      • ROW_LENGTH

        public static final java.lang.Integer ROW_LENGTH
        The default row length (in terms of spaces) used by the data when printed. It is calculated as follows 3 * 25 for 3 zones which are 25 characters (spaces) long + 5 for the column separators "|" as defined in ItemEntity and statically imported here + 4 for the first zone which contains the printed item number on the printed list.

      • addItem

        public java.lang.Boolean addItem(ItemEntity item,
                                 java.lang.Boolean isAuthorized)
        Adds items to the ArrayList using this.add(ItemEntity).

        The function will only add an item if the item does not contain alcohol, or the item contains alcohol but is authorized to be added.

        Parameters:
        item - the item to be added.
        isAuthorized - a boolean representing whether an item is authorized to be added or not
        Returns:
        boolean value signifying the success of the add operation. returns true if either one of the conditions detailed above are met.
